Let $n\geq 2$. Is there a space $S$ of dimension $n$ such that $S^2$ also has dimension $n$?



The space of rational points in Hilbert space has this property for $n=1$. This was proved for general $n$ by Anderson and Keisler \cite{AnKe67}.




References


[AnKe67] Anderson, R. D. and Keisler, J. E., An example in dimension theory. Proc. Amer. Math. Soc. (1967), 709--713.
